value.0: Huh?
You are most welcome here, <FirstName>. I am the Seer. I have awaited your arrival with great anticipation. Please, come... do not be alarmed.

Comment.value: second part of Seer's dialogue (for breaking up if skipped)

value.0: I am sure you have many questions, but there is much we must tell you first. It is important you know something of the Valsharess, if you are to help us against her.
I am glad you are being reasonable about this, for we must work together if we are to defeat our common foe.

Comment.value: third part of Seer's dialogue (for breaking up if skipped)

value.0: I believe it is time for our guest to learn more of the Valsharess, herself. Nathyrra, if you would be so kind...?
Of course, Seer. <StartAction>[She bows her head in acceptance, then steps forward and begins to speak.]</Start>
The drow have ever been ruled by the Matron Mothers who head the great houses. The Valsharess was once one of these: ruthless and powerful in her art, but no more so than any other Matron Mother.
But then Lolth, the Queen of Spiders and goddess of the drow, disappeared... and drow society was thrown into utter chaos. The Valsharess seized on this opportunity.
She summoned a powerful Duke of the Nine Hells, an archdevil she bound to her service. Drawing on this enslaved devil's power, she became a conqueror of the Underdark.
Once the Underdark is hers, she will turn her attention once more to the surface. She believes herself a Queen... a Valsharess, by our tongue... and her ambition knows no end.
It involves you because she wants you dead.
Not long ago, the devil she had enslaved warned the Valsharess that there was one who could defeat her. She ordered an augury and was presented with an image of you.
I had the same dream. <StartAction>[The Seer sighs.]</Start> For whatever reason, destiny has singled you out as the instrument of the Valsharess's defeat.
Destiny has decreed that you alone can stop the Valsharess... which gives us all the more reason to support you.
That we do not know. Perhaps through some artifact or some long forgotten ritual. But whatever her methods, the results cannot be denied.
The priestesses of Lolth are powerless before her, and the great drow houses have bent knee, just as many of the other Underdark races have been intimidated into joining her cause.
Yes, that is a good question. What are we to do now?

Comment.value: final part of Seer's dialogue (for breaking up if skipped)

value.0: There is only one thing that I can do. I must put my faith in the goddess... and that means putting our faith in you. Our fate lies in your hands.
Are you sure, Seer? What do we really know about this...  this <man/woman>? <He/She> could be the death of us all!
Our lives are irrelevant, good Valen. The Valsharess must be stopped at all costs, and <FirstName> is the key to stopping her.
You know I don't believe in your ways, Seer. I won't throw away my life by blindly following anyone, and I don't think anyone here should, either.
You have saved us more times than I can count, Valen. But the army of the Valsharess will soon march against us, and even your great skill in battle will not be enough to save us.
I'm willing to defer to your judgement for now, Seer. But what makes you think this <race> stranger can stop the army of the Valsharess?
<FirstName>, I know you are a <class> of great power. But you are so much more than this. You alone can save us from the Valsharess.
All the drow here in Lith My'athar will stand against the Valsharess, she is the one enemy common to us all. But even our united strength will not be able to defeat her massive army.
Our only hope is for you to find some way to strengthen our forces, as well as weaken the Valsharess and her allies. I will elaborate on this.

The beholders in this area are allied with the Valsharess. Although I do not think that she commands many of these beholders, even a single one is quite formidable. Each of them carries the ability to fire magical rays from its eyestalks which have varying effects. All of them come from a single hive located somewhere in the northern Underdark. If we destroy the hive mother ruling over them, the colony will collapse and the Valsharess will lose their support.

There used to be a passage just north of Lith My'athar that we think connected to the Beholder lair, but recently Formians have moved in and are causing us trouble from the same tunnels. It might yet be easier to reach the Beholder lair from this passage than a frontal assault through their main entrance.
In fact, I be grateful if you could exterminate the Formians for us, as due to the conflict we lack the resources to do it ourselves.
The creatures you call mind flayers are a race of telepaths, capable of reading thoughts and controlling minds. They are known for keeping a horde of dominated thralls as servants and guards.

The Valsharess has many illithid in her army, so it is likely she has recruited the aid of several Overminds. Somewhere in the Underdark is Zorvak'Mur, a small illithid colony. If we can find the Zorvak'Mur Overmind, perhaps it could be persuaded to convince the other Overminds to withdraw their support.
Hopefully, you can find a way to strengthen our own forces as well. They say there is an island inhabited by powerful golems; these would be particularly useful against the Valsharess and her army.
Speak with Cavallas. He can be found on the Eastern side of our base. He will be able to transport you to that island.
Long life and blessed be, my friend.

In my visions you seemed like a more powerful <class> than you are now: that must be a sign of what you will become. I would still ask your assistance against the Valsharess, but please, go carefully until you are more experienced. You alone can save us from the Valsharess, but you might not yet have the power to do so.

Comment.value: After the whole initial scene with the Seer, this is her regular dialogue which she has until the beginning of the Siege

value.0: I trust all goes well. Have you any news to report? Have you made any progress in your efforts to weaken the Valsharess and her followers?
As it happens, yes. The tunnels north of Lith My'atar are once again infested by Formians, and we lack the resources to deal with them.
I would appreciate it if you could kill the hive's Queen for us.
Thank you, <FirstName>.
<StartCheck>[Failure]</Start> I am sorry, <FirstName>, but with my powers of divination I know that you have not done it yet. But I also know that you will return here when you have.
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> You have? This is either a lucky omen, or you possess some powers of foresight yourself. Please, take this gold as a reward.

Yes, or rather, there was. To the southeast of here is a passage through the volcanic Mount Hotenow, which was sealed and protected by the Drow. But with the rise of the Valasharess, we were not able to protect it and the gate was overrun by the Duergar, no doubt in search of rare volcanic minerals.
The key to unlock the gate is undoubtedly still somewhere around the passage entrance, most likely in the hands of the Duergar. If you retrieved it, you could use the passage as you please.
As with all matters here in the Underdark, such a task in dangerous, and it pains me to see our saviour willing to leave, but I have faith that you will return to the Underdark when you are ready.
As it happens, possibly. There are tunnels north of Lith My'athar which have become infested with Formians, but we think that beyond they may connect to the Beholder's lair.
The Formians are proving troublesome, and with the war with the Valsharess we lack the resources to deal with it ourselves. I would greatly appreciate it if you could also exterminate the Formians.
Very well. I will attune you to this temple.
There must be some mistake. You see, you are already attuned to this temple.
Is there anything else that you require of me, then?
Long life and blessed be.
Very well. I will answer what questions I can. Hopefully my knowledge can be useful to you in some way.
Nothing more than what you already know. Her army is still massing. If you do not find some way to weaken her forces before the coming battle, I doubt we will be able to stand against her.
Deep beneath your surface lands exists a vast realm of caverns and blackest lakes that collectively we call the Underdark.

It is here that the drow rule alongside such other creatures as the illithids and the beholders and the duergar. The Underdark is a place of evil and terror, make no mistake... every step must be taken carefully, here.
More specifically, we are in a very remote drow settlement called Lith My'athar on the far side of the great Lake of Memory. Our forces are relatively safe here... until the Valsharess comes.
I won't lie to you, <FirstName>. Our collection of rebels here is nothing against the power of the Valsharess. We have been doing little but running up to this point.
Here in Lith My'athar we have decided to make our stand... but we know we stand little chance against the mighty force that has aligned itself with the Valsharess.
The duergar are gray-skinned cousins to the hargluk, the surface dwarves. They are a dour and industrious folk more prone to cunning and wickedness than their surface brethren.

I am surprised you do not know. You are a hargluk... the duergar are your gray-skinned cousins who live in the Underdark. They are a dour and industrious folk more prone to cunning and wickedness than others of your kind.

The duergar have many reasons to hate the drow intensely, but many of their kind are mercenary enough to hire themselves out to whoever has the wealth to offer them... and the Valsharess is one of those.
They resemble floating eyeballs with many eye-stalks, and each of their eyes can fire a blast with a different magical power. Pain, slowness, petrification... even disintegration.
There is no limit to how often they can use these abilities, so be wary. Should you ever find yourself in their tunnels, it is best to find a way back out as quickly as possible.
Dangerous monsters with blank eyes and tentacles for a mouth. Your kind calls them 'mind flayers', as well, I believe.
They are most cunning and able to use powers of the mind to stun you and render you helpless... at which point they would feast upon your brain, if given a chance. Or make you into a mindless thrall.
I was not always known as such, my friend. A very long time ago I was the daughter of a major house and as ambitious to gain my own power as any other respectable drow.
That was not meant to be, however. I found the worship of my lady Eilistraee, and she has gifted me with visions that have aided her followers.
And so I am called the Seer, for so many years now that my original name has all but been forgotten. In any case, that life is behind me. Now I serve Eilistraee.
I see what my goddess grants me the wisdom to see. I saw that the drow would devolve into chaos, and that the Valsharess would arise out of it.
I see the destiny of my people as it will be, and our place in it. That is why we have returned to the Underdark from our adopted home on the surface.
We are different in the sense that we chose to abandon the society of cruelty and hatred that we were raised in. Our own kind revile us and would hunt us, if they could.
I lead my fellow followers of Eilistraee, yes, though not all the drow gathered here believe as I do. Many of the drow here do not follow Eilistraee at all, though I am one of my Lady's chosen.
I am a drow. I am used to distrust of many kinds. If you give me the opportunity, however, I am certain to prove a valuable ally even if you do not desire a friend.
Yes, quite a number more are outside in the camp. The Valsharess, however, commands several magnitudes more than we do.
Why should it? I require no one to worship as I do, and you are not here on a religious crusade, are you?
Know, however, that you are no pawn of mine nor do I expect to lead you. What you do is of your own free will.
Many do not know it, but not all of the drow are evil. Our Lady Eilistraee is the mistress of song and dance, and it is she who refuses to allow joy and goodness to be taken from us forever.

She is our redemption, and all of us journeyed to the surface lands to be free of the darkness that shackled us. The fact that we are in the Underdark once more to serve her cause is an irony not lost on us.
That is because it isn't. This is a temple to the spider goddess, Lolth, that we have taken refuge in. I am sure she will not mind.
Lolth has disappeared. Her priestesses cast no spells and the society she controlled with an iron fist has fallen to pieces with her absence.
This chaos is what the Valsharess has taken advantage of and has allowed her to achieve such power. As to whether Lolth will return..." <StartAction>[She shrugs.]</Start> "... who can say?"
The Valsharess threatens more than just the Underdark with her schemes, as you well know. She threatens us all, and Eilistraee's chosen stand amongst those ready to stop her.
We are not alone, thankfully. Others have joined us to stop the Valsharess, though they do not believe in the goddess as we do. Ultimately, however, we fight for the same thing.
Common sense, I would hope. At the very least, we both possess a common foe in the Valsharess and that, if nothing else, should stay your blade.
And if not that, how about the fact that you are surrounded by an army of drow... an army that can be turned against an intruder in the blink of an eye.
But my intent is not to threaten you. We must work together, <FirstName>.
All those who stand against the Valsharess have gathered here in Lith My'athar, united in our common desire to see her stopped. Many of the drow here are followers of my Lady Eilistraee.
But there are others, too. Lith My'athar is the ancestral home of House Maeviir, one of the many drow families that has been forced to flee the cities because of the Valsharess.
The followers of House Maeviir now stand with us against the Valsharess, though in other circumstances they would never ally themselves with the followers of Eilistraee.
It is not my nature to speak ill of those who side with us, but I will admit that House Maeviir is not the most desirable of allies. There is tension and mistrust on both sides.
But we have little choice. The Valsharess has a vast army; we need allies if we are to stand against her. House Maeviir recognizes this, and that is why they tolerate our presence here.
For now, the threat of the Valsharess is enough to ensure my followers and those who support House Maeviir will set aside their hatred of each other and focus on our common foe.
Yes, I can. Which ability do you want to enhance?
May Eilistraee grant you beauty.
May Eilistraee grant you wisdom.
May Eilistraee grant you intellect.
May Eilistraee grant you endurance.
May Eilistraee grant you agility.
May Eilistraee grant you strength.
As you wish. Stand still for a moment, please...
Excellent work, <FirstName>. Thank you for your help, and here is your reward.

The golems are powerful creatures. Thank you, <FirstName>... I am certain they will be of great aid to us in the battle to come. For a reward, I can offer this ring: may it protect you from harm in your adventures.

The golems are powerful creatures. Thank you, <FirstName>... I am certain they will be of great aid to us in the battle to come. For a reward, I can offer this ring: may it protect you from harm in your adventures.
Excellent work, <FirstName>! The beholders are formidable foes. If the Valsharess has been denied their aid, she has been severely weakened. I hope this ring helps you in times of danger.
I'm glad the illithid will not be marching against us, though I hope the bargain you struck with them is one we do not regret later. Sometimes we are forced to choose the lesser of two evils.
Have you word of anything else?
There is still much to be done. You have my thanks for your efforts so far, however.
Zesyyr now controls House Maeviir? Then, I must assume Myrune is dead. Why did you do this, <FirstName>?
Yes, you are probably right. Myrune was desperately trying to cling to power. If she had the opportunity to bow before the Valsharess and live, she would.
Perhaps your actions here will be for the greater good. I just hope that Zesyyr shows us more loyalty than she showed her own mother.

value.0: Wait a second... who are you? What's going on here?
You awaited my arrival? How did you know I was coming or who I am?
Then tell me what I need to know.
So how does all this involve me?
I will do whatever I can to end such evil. She has reason to fear me.
It seems the Valsharess and I are on a collision course.
How did she bind an archdevil to her service?
What do you propose we do now?
Like I said earlier, I can help you and your people if the reward is right.
I'll be going now.
I won't fail you, Seer.
I am honored by the faith you've put in me, Seer.
I don't understand... what is it you expect me to do?
I will do whatever I can to stop her evil.
I can help you, but the reward better be worth it.
Do you have any work for me?
If it will help against the Valsharess, I shall do my best.
<StartCheck>[Bluff]</Start> I have just returned from killing the Formian Queen.
Is there another way back to the surface?
Is there another way to the Beholder lair?
Please set me to respawn in Lith My'athar.
I have nothing to report right now.
I should go.
I have some questions for you.
Can you tell me anything else about the Valsharess?
Tell me about the Underdark.
You mentioned the Valsharess coming?
Tell me more about the duergar?
Tell me more about the beholders.
Tell me more about the illithid.
Why are you called the Seer?
I want to ask you something else.
Tell me about your visions.
So you are different than most other drow?
So you lead these drow, then? Are you a priestess?
I don't trust prophets, much.
There are other drow here?
The fact that I worship a different god doesn't worry you?
Tell me about Eilistraee.
This doesn't look like a temple of good.
She won't mind? What makes you say that?
What do you mean by 'serving her cause'?
You're all drow. What's to stop me from killing you all now?
I'd like to know more about my allies here.
Do you think you can trust them?
That probably makes for some tension.
Can you please give me a buff?
Actually, I don't need a buff right now.
Charisma.
Wisdom.
Intelligence.
Constitution.
Dexterity.
Strength.
I need some healing.
Tell me what is needed again.
I have eliminated the Formians outside Lith My'athar.

That's all for now.
I helped Zesyyr seize control of House Maeviir.
Myrune would have betrayed us to the Valsharess.
